This Privacy Policy explains how Telegram Sticker Bot (“the Bot,” “we,” “our,” or “us”) collects, uses, and protects information when you use our service on Telegram.

1. Information We Collect

The Bot does not require you to create an account or provide personal details such as your name or email.
When you interact with the Bot, we may automatically receive:

Your Telegram user ID (a numeric identifier Telegram provides to bots).

Messages and files you voluntarily send to create or manage sticker packs.

Basic technical data automatically provided by Telegram (such as message timestamps and server logs).

No other personal data is collected.

2. How We Use Your Information

The limited information we receive is used only to:

Create and manage your sticker packs.

Deliver stickers and bot responses back to you.

Maintain the stability and security of the service.

We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties.

3. Data Storage and Retention

Sticker pack data (images and related metadata) is stored only as long as necessary for the Bot to function.

Telegram servers may retain messages according to Telegram’s Privacy Policy
.

You may request deletion of sticker data linked to your Telegram ID by contacting us (see Section 6).

4. Third-Party Services

The Bot operates entirely within the Telegram platform.
Your interactions are subject to Telegram’s own data handling practices, which are described in Telegram’s Privacy Policy
.

5. Children’s Privacy

This service is not directed to children under the age of 13.
We do not knowingly collect information from children.
If you believe a child has provided information to the Bot, please contact us so we can delete it.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions or wish to request deletion of your data, please contact:

Email: telegramstickerbot.support@gmail.com
